The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
 Build a house, block neighbours door
 PROGRESS PATH: Construction material dumped on the pavement. Pictures by Kishor Roy Chowdhury P.K. Chowdhury: In some blocks, contractors stock building materials on the pavements near the construction sites, crippling movement of traffic. Is there no way to stop this?This is really a public nuisance. We find stacks of sand, bricks and other building material dumped all around, with not a care for other residents of the township. To stop this, the police need block committees and the municipality to work together.  Copyright 
